{#      <p class="govuk-body">The defendant might:</p>#}
{#      <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">#}
{#        <li>Plead guilty to all the charges. Plead guilty means they say they did the crimes.</li>#}
{#        <li>Plead guilty to some of the charges.</li>#}
{#        <li>Plead not guilty to all of the charges.</li>#}
{#      </ul>#}
{#      <p class="govuk-body">If the defendant pleads guilty, the case will proceed to sentencing.</p>#}
{#      <p class="govuk-body">The Witness Care Unit will tell you the sentence.</p>#}
{#      <p class="govuk-body">You will be referred to the Victim Contact Scheme if the offender is sentenced to over 12 months or to a hospital order for a violent or sexual crime.</p>#}
{#      <p class="govuk-body">If the defendant pleads not guilty, a trial date will be set.</p>#}

{#      <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">Stage 5: The court trial</h2>#}
{#      <p class="govuk-body">The Witness Care Unit will assess your needs and support you before the trial. They may refer you to the Witness Service.</p>#}
{#      <p class="govuk-body">On the day of the trial you may have to go to court to give evidence.</p>#}
{#      <p class="govuk-body">You can get extra support called Special Measures if you need help you give evidence.</p>#}
{#      <p class="govuk-body">The Witness Care Unit will tell you the verdict once it has been reached.</p>#}
{#      <p class="govuk-body">The outcome could be:</p>#}
{#      <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">#}
{#        <li>The defendant is found guilty and the case proceeds to sentencing. If the offender appeals their sentence you will be told.</li>#}
{#        <li>The defendant is found not guilty and you may be referred to support services.</li>#}
{#      </ul>#}

{#      <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">Stage 6: After the trial</h2>#}
{#      <p class="govuk-body">You can join the Victim Contact Scheme if the offender is sentenced to over 12 months or to a hospital order for a violent or sexual crime.</p>#}
{#      <p class="govuk-body">You will receive updates throughout the offender's sentence from the Victim Contact Scheme.</p>#}
{#      <p class="govuk-body">You will be told when the offender is released.</p>#}
{#      <p class="govuk-body">The offender might be considered for parole (early release).</p>#}
{#      <p class="govuk-body">You can give your views on parole conditions and write a Victim Personal Statement for the Parole Board.</p>#}
{#      <p class="govuk-body">You will be told the Parole Board's decision.</p>#}
